PREAMBLE
The goals of the Open Font License (OFL) are to stimulate worldwide 
development of collaborative font projects...

The OFL allows the licensed fonts to be used, studied, modified and 
redistributed freely as long as they are not sold by themselves.

DEFINITIONS
"Font Software" refers to the set of files released under this license.
"Reserved Font Name" refers to names specified after the copyright statement.
"Original Version" refers to the collection of Font Software components.
"Modified Version" refers to any derivative made by modifying components.
"Author" refers to contributors to the Font Software.

PERMISSION & CONDITIONS
1) The Font Software may not be sold by itself.
2) Original or Modified Versions may be bundled or sold with software.
3) Modified Versions may not use Reserved Font Names without permission.
4) Copyright Holder and Author names may not be used to promote derivatives.
5) The Font Software must be distributed under this license only.

